,Recommended,269730,17174546,"Posted: 22 July, 2015",all,Pave,"((I wanted to add this info to top afterwards, since I failed to mention this before:Unless one specifically goes offline or play the offline-single-player-mode ""Seasons"", all the shots are recorded to online-storages, which is really amazing to me considering I've gotten to a point I semi-refuse to play ""hitscan-client-side-detection-only""-games and such without replay-systems nowadays.Unfortunately currently the replay-system is very barebones with only the playback option available, this far-cry to systems like ""Mario Golf Advance + Toadstool""-tour had.But hopefully this system will get further improved in the sequel / 2.0-update (AKA. ""The Golf Club 2"").))The Overview:Alright, since the game currently is more closer to ""complete""-golf-game nowadays, I suppose it's finally a time to give an overview on this title.First of, what ""The Golf Club"" is:- ""Bare-bones ""just golf""""-game with emphasis on simulation.What ""The Golf Club"" is not:- ""Arcade-like""-golf game with ""Career""-modes to become stronger, more ""bling"", or anything else similar: It's ""Just-golf"".I personally have nicknamed this game as ""Tiger Woods PGA Tour Online ""without gorilla-suit"" and with perma-TrueSwing-mode""; not much else to comment about that aside that both games are / were quite well built into Unity3D-engine.((Those who are interested though, the ""Tiger Woods PGA Tour 12 - Masters"" is quite similar both the UI and the golf-play-wise, minus of course the (identical) ""Greens Fee"" and other things that were in ""PGA Tour Online.""))In other words for the most part your avatar customization is mainly limited to ""etique""-abiding outfits.And your golf-equipments are standardized performance-wise, meaning that there are no ""power-golf-clubs"". There might be more ""style-suiting"" equipment-options available in future (E.G slightly more wider+lighter-clubs to allow pitching from tougher spots with less ""carry"" due lessened-weight), but that's just one personal wishful-thinking.((Fair to mention that I personally mainly play with the least amount of ""assistance-UI"" as possible (green-grid, shot-direction-reticle, wind-indicator, and such), to which I base my overview on))As hinted earlier, the players are also limited to ""semi-TrueSwing"" system, since it's by design that there is no ""traditional 3-click-system"" in-game to emphasis on more ""feeling""-gameplay instead of being cold-hard-mechanical.Unfortunately at the moment, there is no ""dry-hitting"" so playing by just ""the feel"" alone isn't necessarily working for the favor of the players.And since the ""hitting-indicator"" isn't currently working exactly in real-time either (it appears only after the hit is done), the game turns unfortunately into quite fiddly ""percentage""-game because players are semi-forced to number-crunch with the ""lofts"" of their clubs if they want to make more accurate shots. So in the end the hitting-game (currently) is mainly limited to adjusting the loft of the clubs and hitting with max-power, since for the most part the ""fine-tune-club-action"" seen in various other ""TrueSwing""-game is quite non-existent.Point being, the swing+putting-system could be better since it's currently heavily dependant on ""power"" only (indicated by how ""back"" you ""Pull"" the clubs). But it suffices, somewhat.As for the courses (of the amount which in theory are infinite), I personally can only give a / some warning(s): Given that the major-amount of the courses are done by ""everyday-non-pro""-players, there are going to large amount of courses not following the ""official"" (real-life) recommendations; This is very important thing to remember, especially if you're into regular tournament participations.- Especially before the ""Out-of-Bounds"" (or ""O.B"")-system was implemented in, there is large amount of ""Trap-courses"", meaning that if you are very unfortunate to hit your ball into one of the ""trap-valleys"", you're going to be guaranteed end-up getting that ""+9"" (or any other ""max-hit""-amount set).- Since the game doesn't yet support the ""cup-place-randomization"", you're going to end seeing a huge amount of these placed in the middle of ""spiral-macaroni""-greens.What I am trying to say is the a quite a little amount of course-designers follow the following recommendation: ""A player putting from above the hole should be able to stop the ball near the hole."" Okay, that is just one part of the whole thing....For those who are interested for more info, here are few links:http://www.barryrhodes.com/2011/11/position-of-hole-on-putting-green.htmlhttp://www.randa.org/en/Rules-and-Amateur-Status/Guidance-on-Running-a-Competition.aspx?chapter=4&section=2In overall, ""The Golf Club"" is a nice change in the golf-game scenery in which you can simply jump-in and jump-out freely without need of worrying whether your have enough good ""gear"" or otherwise ""stats"" to simply play both by yourself and competing with other players.The issues mentioned above aside, the gameplay itself is pretty solid.And this game  isn't all that power-demanding alongside the game itself is being quite stable (at least on my quite low-spec-computer).On a extra note, the game also features a quite extensive API for those people who'd like to make more organized leagues and similar organizations.This allows websites such astgctours.comto have more accurate data on the players themselves.Who knows though what the developers will eventually bring to this game; the possibilities are almost unlimited!"
,Recommended,269730,15587638,"Posted: 27 April, 2015",all,reinhardtw,"Being a avid golfer in real life playing of an +2 handicap myself I have played most of the golf games out there. And to be honest most of them become boring because they are way to easy to master. The golf club however always seems to have a new challenge up its sleeve.I have read many reviews slamming the inconsistency of playing with your mouse. My experience is that yes it is challenging but fair. I have played and struggled but learned with each round (Pro Tip, get yourself a proper mouse and a good gaming mouse pad I recommend a Gamdias Pad). Through practice and practice you can achieve amazing things and compete without a gamepad or building a swing rail(cheating in my opinion.). Now my in game handicap is at +9 and getting better(Just shot a 55 at Flathead).You would think that if you played off a +9 you have mastered the game, but you would be mistaken. In elite tournaments playing on your handicap will only just get you in the top 50. Its all about the quest we as golfers share but never attain...Perfection.The quest to be the best and the opportunity to really compete with thousands of other golfers is what makes the golfers club an amazing golf game.Now to the game play. Is it perfect? No, there are problems, especially regarding the rules. With rules I refer to the lack of dropping in the game when you are unfortunate enough to land in a water hazard of end up in an unplayable lie. Most times the re-hit option is enforced only on a rare occasion does the game will drop for you. As for the unplayeble situation, it play it as it lies(or restart ;-) ) There is no custom drop option which is annoying.(They have rectified the droping problem with the last update!04/05/2015)How do you become good? Swinging straight is only 10pecent of the battle. You really have to think about you shot: Club selection, Shot Type, Height, Shape and the most important part of all, where do you want to hit the next shot from. Especially when it comes to where you what to putt from. Speed and rythm of your swing is also very important. Don't think a fast back and through will do it or get you more distance.The Golf Club is an Awsome golf game and I feel it is one of my best purchases on steam to date. I can't wait for the Seasons DLC to come out. No problem with buying it as a add on. I feel I have gotten more that my moneys worth so far.Highly recommended!!!!! You get out what you put in just like in real life golf!"
