,Recommended,269730,15599876,"Posted: 28 April, 2015",all,cerox,"This piece of art has tremendous potential. I am thankful to the developers for a lovely game where I can play a large amount of golf between writing mission critical code and working on my software developments (relaxation much). What makes this game excellent is:1. The swing mechanic isn't newcomer friendly. The swing has a learning curve, you MUST pull your mouse backwards and then forwards to thrust your shots. This step done by you controlling your hand, wrist and arm need be precise for perfect shots otherwise you will inherit a large handicap. The handicap can be thought as a rank, the lower the handicap, the better your precision in this game I conclude.The game plots a linear traversal of your mouse movement per shot, thus you can see if you need improve pulling back or pushing forward to maintain a straight swing of each club.2. Each club is distinct, each has its own feel and each has a distinct difficulty to master.3. The game is not arcade-like, it caters to a hardcore gamer. Thus it may be considered in time a golf variant eSports title, much like Counter Strike is to professional FPS players.4. MAPS! The game includes real-world golf courses thus adding more realism. The game also includes algorithms so that, a) other players can create courses and upload them for other players to play and b) you can play a new course in literally seconds thus new content additions driven by the community for the community.A sound financial investment for years of golf playing for those of us struck at our desk. Try it, when you get the hang of it, its fun.---Things I'd like to see in future.1. Graphical Settings, I would like to tweak all settings, my computer is a beast and I want to see what is enabled when I've set the game launch settings to HIGH.2. Frame Rendering when Window is Inactive. I play in windowed mode and not fullscreen, thus when I window switch to a work window, I want to be able to see frame updates in the game window (which is inactive) without having to click on it again. This is useful when in multiplayer, watching others play etc whilst I can write some more code inbetween my shots.3. Customisation options, character customisation etc."
