76561197970962260,Recommended,269730,18549064,"Posted: 18 October, 2015",all,theloneginger,"Graphics are brilliant and it's very atmospheric (geese swimming on the water, rabbits running around, birds singing, etc)I use an Xbox 360 controller for windows and the swing with the right joystick feels good and I find it reasonably easy to control. The straighter you move the stick backwards and forwards, the straighter your shot. The putting takes a bit of getting used to, but after a while you get a feel for it, just like real golf.You can also enter tournaments which other players online play in and there is a season mode, which is a DLC which has various difficulties which you unlock by completing the one before.I'd really like them to have put in a driving range and putting green option for practicing, but other than that the game is brilliant."
76561198009761410,Recommended,269730,29307378,Posted: 16 January,all,Unzy,"Picked this up when on sale and it's probably the best golf game on PC currently.There is a learning curve, and i like that. Having to think about club choice taking into account all the variables like the lie, wind and other hazardsandhaving to manage the power of the stroke without a 'power bar' to aid you adds that extra level of skill which i love.The game looks pretty great as well, but there are some occasional visual glitches with the terrain. On my system i had to bring the tree count down a bit, but 60+fps is easy with a gtx 970. The physics seem pretty solid to me as well, although approach shots sometimes seem to roll forever.There are some improvements for issues which in reality boil down to just a lack of polish which i think should be rectified for The Golf Club 2 in 2017:UI - Not too bad visually but not the nicest to navigate intuitively. There should be more search options when selecting courses and a 'played' counter/ filter so you can find courses you've not yet played easily.Player progression - Only limited customisation of a few clothing items. I can understand the lack of player progression as that makes it more like TWPGA games, however i think adding this and more personalisation options such as clubs would add something extra to the single-player mode especially.Sync - When playing with a buddy online there are sometimes issues with what i'm seeing vs what my friend sees, eg. frequently you miss a putt by a tiny amount but it goes in on their screen).Course creator - Because of the UI, designing and building a course takes so long because the UI is a nightmare to navigate. Has potential though.No Windowed borderless mode - lack of is annoying as the windowed mode won't snap to your screen and defaults to taking up half of each screen on a 2 monitor setup, meaning you have to drag it, and tabbing out of game in fullscreen mode makes the game run at <5fps when you come back in.TLDR: Solid golf game, tough but fun and definitely worth buying in a sale. At this point you may as well wait until TGC2.7.5/10"
