,Recommended,269730,21097929,"Posted: 10 February, 2016",all,Vitality,"Vitality’s S&T ReviewsShort and Tasty… The Bits that matterShort StoryGet your score cards out because this is a HOLE-IN-ONE!OverviewThe Golf Club is a golf simulation video game developed by HB Studios on the Unity game engine. It is a golf sim, boasting a powerful Course Creator based on the procedural generation of courses. The Course Creator can generate a brand new course in seconds which can be shared and played immediately online with friends and other gamers.Vitality’s ThoughtsThese mixed reviews are SERIOUSLY insane! I was very hesitant on actually purchasing, But boy am I glad I did.I'm coming from Tiger Woods 08, And I seamlessly transferred into this modern take on the sport without any issues.People complain about the putting, but again I have no problem with it. Yes it takes getting used too, but come on this is a GOLF simulator, People realise how FRUSTRATING this game can be right ?There's a few negatives I do have with it though, When I play 4 player game modes and we create and edit the player names I would like the system to remember the names I've set for them and there outfits, So We don't have to customise them every few days we are going to be playing. Right now it just defaults them to (Name_1) not the name I've set for them.I also wish I could disable the ball following lines, and also speed up the ball when in mid flight.This game IS GOOD though, I don't think it's exactly worth the $40 price tag, and the way they sell stuff can be a little dodgy, as the season mode is a paid DLC but they're minor, If you can get the game for under $30 it's well worth it.Pros:Amazing Graphics, Wildlife, And PlantsGreat Simulation of a frustrating sportCourse creation is amazing, You'll never get bored playing the same 10 coursesThe Commentator isn't generic and annoying like most gamesWon't cost you $50 for a pack of real balls to lose in the creekCons:Player Customisation is limiting4 Player mode should save custom playersSome HUD options for lines etc would be nicePricing is a little dumb founding. (I believe in DLC, But for Season mode?)ConclusionGreat golf simulator, Probably the best on the market right now, I would highly recommend the game to any avid golfer or anyone who wants to play a golf sim, Don't look at the game though if you're after an arcade Tiger woods though. I'd also recommend the game be purchased under $30, But if you've got the money you won't be  disappointed.79/100"
76561198112037188,Recommended,269730,17099125,"Posted: 17 July, 2015",all,bob,"Look at my hours played, well over 1000, so I can't possibly give this game a bad review. I love the game, but it's simplistic, basic, and lacks almost every option you can imagine. I am a casual video golfer, I want to hit most fairways, hit most of the greens and score better than par. It is pretty easy to do that in this game.Read the reviews and System Requirements, this game renders the whole course at once, so no load times between holes, but you need a beefy pc to play it the way it was intended and you MUST have version 11 of Direct XPros/cons depending on how you look at it:There are basically no options in this game, I don't really ever see many options in its future, it is just a simple golfgame where you can relax and play a round of golf like an average joe on the weekend.Everyone uses the same clubs, you can only drive the ball about 270 yards without wind, but you will get wind as they won't give you the option to play without it.The game currently has over 70 thousand user courses, but not easy searching for the ones you will enjoy playing.The Greg Norman Course Creator is an awesome addition as I enjoy playing a different course every time I play, this is a good thing as very few courses warrant a second play.No lobby for multiplayer, but you can play a friends ghost ball or play a live friend with almost real time results.Putter - Putting feels greatWoods - driving is brainless, you can do it while argueing with the wife, if you can move the control stick backward and then forward you will be a star.Irons - I like themChipping and Flops is probably way too easy for most hard core golf gamers.Rating:Gameplay - 7/10Graphics - 7/10Fun - 8/10Golf Options to make this a great game. 2/10Manual or ingame tutorial - None - 0/10Optimized - Game runs on the Unity Engine, either the engine is weak or a bad choice to render whole course at once or their coders can't optimize it as they seem to dummy stuff down with each new addition, like the engine can't handle anymore or the code is running amok. 3/10I guess this game is a buyer's beware game, you'll either love it or it will run like a 2 legged dog.I really enjoy this game. Yes, I think it could be better with some freakin' Options, but that ain't gonna happen.My overall rating would be 6.5, but I really enjoy this game and I have to play on medium with a Windows7 Home Premium, service pack 1, AMD FX 8120 Eight core processor, 3.10 Ghz, 8Gb Ram, 64bit OS, Nvidia Geforce GTX 560 2 GB card.OK. Now go buy this game, but don't come running to me if it doesn't run on your PC. I am a glass half-empty type person so your mileage may vary."
