76561198058300124,Recommended,269730,9908639,"Posted: 23 April, 2014",all,Maverick,"First impression had my GPU running pretty hard. 670gtx, 75 celcius, 38 fps. It'll get better but it is.... Unity... apparently. I was on the high settings so no real drama this early on.But the golf. Ahhh... The golf.Links 386. This is how far I go back in this genre so I can pretty well say I've been there, done that. Tried them all, even down to the Wii with my kids. Those bulbous heads and stupid haircuts really made me laugh. Really. This is *golf* and you look like an idiot!!Oops... Sorry. I digress.There's something very, very different about this golf sim. You need to actually plan and play your shots PROPERLY. Got that? PROPERLY.There's no little swing indicators and clicky bits. There's no arbitrary line to STOP for ""maximum power"". This sim does require a finesse of stroke and practise regime like nothing I've ever seen. It's nice.If you're a must.have.line.to.click player this may not be for you. You've been warned.But... but.... this is easy to grasp. Intuitive even.  (although much harder to master if you want that tricky fade around those trees on the 17th).The visuals in this are nice and no doubt the GPU issues will chill a little as optimisations go in.  It is early access at time of writing so I'm not going to scream agghhhhhh with my extra power costs just yet.The commentary is sublime despite an obvious repetiveness if you play badly for prolonged periods. It's sardonic, 19th hole humour if ever. ""John"" has obviously played many a round with many a weekend hack... and it shows. Some may be put off by it. It's down to how you perceive it.I like this game but I suspect it will wear thin quickly. The scores are just arbitrary numbers and the stroke play, while intuitive is well... quite wrong. This is not 8-ball and yet I push vertical while I look at the green. I'm hoping some changes in the future might address this.Worth waiting until final release if you're squeamish spending. A must for golfers with scorecard phobia out on the real course.I'm sure casual golfers will find it pretty easy too - after a few rounds. It's not rocket science. Not on a computer anyway.8.5/10 - gg"
