76561197988749956,Recommended,269730,23428573,"Posted: 6 June, 2016",all,Ultrazen,"Changed this review to positive after fidgeting around with a few things and changing some settings.  TLDR:  The best feel of any golf game ever made.  Not without it's problems, but well worth the money.I used to be a scratch golfer in real life, and my persuit of a great feeling computer golf game has been ongoing since the Links series.  This game has surpassed that, and that's pretty high praise.Pros:1.  Looks decent2.  Ball physics are pretty good3.  Putting and chipping has actual feel, and only feel.  There are no real meters or presets to use.  This is probably the single best thing about the game.Cons:1.  Sluggish.  Feels like it's constanty grinding your computer into the dust, even at lower setting.  Feels poorly optimized.  Still investigating various driver and settings options.  Shadows seem to be some of the biggest problems.2.  Some resolution/display bugs, still tracking some of these down.3.  The menu system.....at first I thought things were just in a menu I couldn't find, turns out that it's just that the feature isn't there lol.  It's very feature light.  No mulligans (easiest way to practice)...I get why they did this, but I think in solo play mode it should be implemented.  Practice in general would be nice.  I know you can go make your own, but a driving range, chipping, and putting would really be a nice addition.4.  My settings issue was actually fixed by a reload so...might have been something that failed to load.  I was intitially having problems with changing density of assets.I'm actually changing this reveiw to a recommended.  The ""feel"" of actually playing golf in this game, is just hands down the best there has ever been.  Even though it's incredibly feature sparse, the core golf mechanics are as close as you are going to get to real life.  Worth the purchase price on that merit alone.This game is a bit frustrating, but I have high hopes for the future.  If the options /modes can be fleshed out a bit, this will certainly go on to be the best golf game produced.  As it stands now, it plays the best of anything.  Nothing has ever captured the feel of putting and chipping like this game does.  You really do develop a sense of what to do just by looking at the course, and not by looking at numbers, that's a major accomplishment."
