,Not Recommended,269730,11788177,"Posted: 19 August, 2014",all,Flaknugget,"I like the social and course building aspects of this game... but the controls, whether using a gamepad and especially when using a mouse and keyboard (I've tried both), are incredibly difficult and need a lot of work before this game will be playable.It is fairly easy to make the perfectly straight 100% power shots every time, so the driving game is almost too easy, but when you need a little finesse, like hitting the ball at 60-90% power, forget it.The distance estimates applied to the clubs can't be trusted, especially on shorter shots like lobs and chips, the distances are frequently off by a few dozen yards.Putting is especially broken, because there is only one power spectrum, 0-105 feet, so if you want to make an 5-10 foot putt, in other words apply 5-10% power, getting anywhere close to correct is virtually impossible, you're just as likely to putt it 30 feet or 2 feet."
