,Recommended,269730,21527015,"Posted: 28 February, 2016",all,The Lovecharger,"This review is coming from someone who has been a player of the Links franchise for over 10 years. I have played a number of other golf games also, but I always found myself going back to Links because of it feeling ""truer"" than other golf games. That is until now, and playing The Golf Club, chances are I'll never be firing Links up again.I have been waiting a while to play TGC, because golf is frustrating at the best of times, so the thought of playing a golf game in early access was something I was certainly not prepared to do. I can only guess that many people did play this in early access though, and that is where the negative reviews have come from. The fact that the reviews are mixed for TGC really, really baffles me.Now TGC is not perfect... The UI is a bit of a nightmare, making it feel like a console port, and no multiplayer lobbies for PUGS is a bit of a shame. Fortunately, TGC is absolutely fantastic when it comes to actually playing golf. The lies are great, the physics fantastic, and the graphics are beautiful. If you are a fan of golf, then this is exactly what you're looking for.I have seen criticism for TGC not including a three click. Well I have being using mouse and keyboard and if you set up your sensitivity to what is suggested then it feels great. Yes there is room for error, like golf, and this room for error brings such great satisfaction out of your good shots. It requires a learning curve which will not take long at all, and trust me, what you get out of this method is far greater than you will with a three-click.I will say though, thatTGCTours.comhas completely made this game great. Here you can register and compete against multiple skill-sets of players, in a real season, with all competions true to the regular professional golf calender. Also remember, every guy you're competing with has the same club bag, and swing, albeit controllers may be used as well as mice. Personally I like the mouse as it requires a more physical ""swing"" than pushing forward an analogue stick. However, it's nice to know that ""three clickers"" aren't dominating leaderboards.The Golf Club is truly a spectacular golfing game, and the community(TGCTours.com)has absolutely rescued the lack of social elements for HBStudios.Wow you've read this far? Go register for qualifying school, earn your card, and go compete. You will not regret it and you won't regret owning TGC."
