76561198241410286,Not Recommended,269730,28994702,Posted: 3 January,all,Trainwreck071302,"I really want to like this game.  It has the potential to be a fantastic golf simulator, but its just a total mess.  Even after being out as long as it has been.  You really roll the dice because from what I've read in other reviews the game either runs great for you or doesn't run at all.  I'm well past the point where I can return it but I wish I had.  From huge spikes and dips in frame rate, to terrain suddenly becoming exaggerated (think small hills becoming mountains) to the whole forest ending up in the sky.  It will run fine for a while, then it will just stop working arbitrarily.  Most recently I just freezes after launch.  This is on a computer that is very much capable of running this game.  Do yourself a favor and stay away.  The game play is great but it's not worth the headaches."
,Recommended,269730,16116025,"Posted: 1 June, 2015",all,khamakazee,"I recommend the game but with hesitation. The single player campaign is severely lacking as far as progression like normal games go. There is a new seasons mode but it's not done very well. You just try and advance, that's it. Where the game truly shines is the created courses. There are hundreds if not thousands of courses to choose from. Too many have high winds but that is supposed to make it challenging. I'd like a better filtering process and I heard it's coming.If you really want to get involved in the game and have some fun join the TGC Tours website(tgctours.com). They host weekly tournaments and the people there are great. You will be placed in a category with the intention of moving up the ladder to the PGA or European tours but best of luck, lots of great players out there.The game itself has a few quirks I'd like to get off my chest. First is the inconsistency at times when using a XBox 360 controller. At least once a round you will have a drive just go sideways on you even though you think you hit a good shot. The fairway bunkers and rough can also be questionable since it's almost always impossible to get a decent approach shot with a chance to get back on the green if you are any distance away. One area that takes skill is putting much like real golf. Only here you will quickly find out most putts seem to be downhill, even when you go past the pin and the return putt is also downhill. Make sense? I'd say about 75% of my putts have a downhill grade to it. I and others have also witnessed the 92% bug that comes up once in awhile. What it means is your swing is at 92%. Doesn't happen often but it does occur. The commentary can get grading at times too. I turn it off now but then it gets even more boring because you have no crowds to cheer you on.The game itself looks good, not great. It does not run very efficiently when I'm checking my CPUID monitor gauges. My guess is because it loads the whole course to make load times non existent. Good trade-ff for some, maybe not for others. The customization of the characters is a bit of a joke. The real meat of the game is the course creation so don't expect any RPG elements here or new gear. The physics and gameplay isn't bad and because I love golf I can give it some leeway since the really isn't much else to play at the moment. There is a new PGA game coming but only for the new consoles so until then this is about it for any sim like golf game.Overall I'd say about a 7/10. Not bad for a first attempt."
