,Recommended,269730,10000524,"Posted: 2 May, 2014",all,mikeandlizmcc,"This is the first game I've ever reviewed, and mainly because it's just that awesome.  It is by far the best golf game I've ever played and it's only early access.  It is truly a golf simulator.  You have no control over the ball in flight, such as top spin or back spin.  All of that gets set up from stance and strike options before you swing, like in real golf.  There is no turbo to super power your shot.  Right now the only customizable options are to customize clothing.  The avatar and abilities do not have customization options yet, but I believe they are on the board to be added.  No stat tracking as yet, but is also to be added.  Which is fine by me...this game is hard, so I have the chance to get used to it before stats start reminding me how much I suck.Graphics are beautiful, especially for the Unity engine.  I get FPS around 30 at the moment, but the dev team continues to release optimization updates almost every week, if not every other week.  It is multiplayer on the same computer as you can add guests and take turns with the same controller.  BTW you definately want to use a controller for this game.  I haven't tried the keyboard mouse combo, but my 360 controller is perfect for gameplay.There is also multiplayer over the net.  You can add a friend to your round and play together.  You don't see you friends avatar yet, but you see the shot they make.  There is about a 5-10 second lag from the time they hit to when you see it.  There are still a few bugs, like when my brother loses a ball in water, it sometimes gets stuck and I can't see him play anymore even though he's still hitting through the course.There are no load times between holes whatsoever.  The entire course is pre-loaded, so in your map view you can see your buddy hit even if he's on a different hole.There is an unlimited amount of golf courses to play through a course creator which is extremely easy to use.  You can have complete control and pour hours and hours into creating your dream course or re-creating your favorite course in real life.  Or you can set up basic options and let the computer generate one on it's own.  You can make a course extremely easy with slow greens, wide open fairways, and no wind, to being a lose-10-balls-every-time-you-play course.It is fully worth the price, in fact I almost always wait for a game to go on sale.  I didn't with this one.  I took a chance and it is definately worth it.  And with all the coming additions to the game, it is going to get even better.If you are a fan of golf, real or digital, this is a must-have golf game.  Better than any Tiger Woods game I ever played.  You won't be disappointed."
